## James Allen Moving to Blue Nile (The Arbitrage Hack)

Signet is sunsetting James Allen’s standalone operation in [August 2026](https://rapaport.com/news/signet-to-close-james-allen-e-commerce-site/), rolling its famous "True Hearts" collection directly into Blue Nile's inventory.

This creates massive price overlap and arbitrage opportunities for savvy buyers who know how to identify the **[diamond cut guide](https://diamondcritics.com/diamond-cut-guide/)** specifications that define an elite stone without paying for the premium label.

### The Audit: Exploiting the "True Hearts" Tax

The impending consolidation has led to a "split-database" phenomenon. Blue Nile is currently listing James Allen inventory alongside its own legacy stock.

Because these two brands historically used different markup strategies, we are finding identical **[diamond 4Cs](https://diamondcritics.com/diamond-4cs/)** configurations with wildly different price tags.

