### The Migration Secret: Pay for the Angles, Not the Name

The "True Hearts" brand is famous for perfect optical symmetry (Hearts & Arrows). However, since the systems are merging, Blue Nile's standard "Ideal" filter now catches many stones that were originally slated for the James Allen premium tier.

By manually auditing the **[diamond cut guide](https://diamondcritics.com/diamond-cut-guide/)** for a 34-35° crown angle and a 40.6-40.9° pavilion angle, you can find a "True Hearts" stone in a "Blue Nile" wrapper.

> 
> 
> Blue Nile is now the sole home for the True Hearts legacy. But here is the secret: You can find "Regular" GIA Excellent stones in the Blue Nile database that mathematically match True Hearts proportions for **25% less**.  
>   
> Never pay for the brand name; pay for the angles. Use the **[diamond price calculator](https://diamondcritics.com/diamond-price-calculator/)** to verify if you are actually getting a deal or just paying for marketing.
