### How to Audit Cloudy SI2s Using the "Breeze" 4K Video

![Blue Nile Breeze 4K video zoom feature at 40x magnification showing how to audit cloudy SI2 diamonds for twinning wisps and inclusions using the interactive 360° diamond inspection tool in 2026.](/images/blue-nile-breeze-4k-video-zoom-cloudy-si2-diamond-audit-2026-1024x683.jpg "Blue Nile Breeze 4k Video Zoom Cloudy Si2 Diamond Audit 2026")

Blue Nile recently updated their interface to the **"Breeze" 4K Video Engine**, a high-fidelity selection tool that is mandatory for 2026 buyers. When shopping for earrings, you must never trust a static stock photo or a paper certificate.

You must utilize the **40x video zoom** to physically audit the diamond for "Clouds" or "Twinning Wisps"—microscopic inclusions that can make a stone look like a piece of salt rather than a diamond.

### The Warning: The "Amazon-ification" of Diamonds

In the race to offer the lowest price, many retailers are participating in the "Amazon-ification" of the industry—listing thousands of lower-grade stones (SI1-SI2) without manual inspection. If you are buying **pre-set earrings** with an SI1 or SI2 clarity grade, you are essentially buying blind.

On the **Blue Nile** platform, the **Breeze UI** is your only defense. If the video looks even slightly hazy or "oily" in the builder, it will look dull on your ear. A "Cloud" inclusion isn't just a spot; it’s a structural fog that traps light, killing the fire of the stone.

